  subhead="Your latest reel is a forty-five-second sequence filmed from the cab of a high-reach excavator — the long boom sweeping across a four-storey former printing works, the concrete pulveriser jaw closing on a reinforced concrete column, the column fracturing and cascading into the exclusion zone below, dust suppression creating a haze, and the final shot pulling back to reveal half the building gone and the crusher feeding on the arisings pile. Twenty-eight thousand views. A developer in North Oxford DMs: 'That is serious kit. We are about to submit planning for a residential development on a brownfield site in Marston. There is a 1970s 2-storey concrete warehouse on it, about 2,500 sqm, plus some hardstanding and underground services. Going to need the lot demolished and cleared to formation level. Can you give us a rough idea of programme and handle the pre-demo asbestos survey too? Planning decision in about 10 weeks.' You are on site. Without AI DMs, the message sits. With it, the AI asks whether the underground services include fuel tanks or contaminated drainage, confirms you coordinate R&D asbestos surveys, and captures the lead — 1970s warehouse, Marston, 2,500 sqm, concrete, hardstanding, underground services, brownfield, formation level, planning in ten weeks."
